This is the pattern I see in the phrasing as well; it likely has a lot to do with genre.

In that way, a remix then implies both in a digital landscape. The rearrangement of existing notes based on your personal style and understanding of the musical piece, with a specific focus on the digital art and tools that make mixing so simple and artistic in this day and age.

While mostly synonymous, there are subtle differences in the meaning based on their represented genre. An arrangement implies a control over the notes being played, as if it were on a classical sheet. A cover more so implies creative interpretations based on personal style.

John’s unwavering commitment made him a forever champion in the fight for economic and social justice. John, our journey continues.

He helped the people do what they had never done before—demand and get a national holiday. That was John’s victory for us. One of my favorite memories is sitting at his keyboard, in his apartment, showing him how to play My Cherie Amour.

I didn’t know that voice and those words would affect my life deeply and we would share that mission together, years later. That mission, the King Holiday, is a symbol of John Conyers’s triumphant legacy.

John Conyers was my friend and hero. When I was 16, I heard his voice for the first time. He was advocating for a holiday for Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. It was a warm, persuasive voice that made such a clear case for us to recognize this day. I never dreamed I would meet him.
